Team
Synergy CHC is built on the strength of a leadership team with decades
of entrepreneurial success and industry expertise. In just under two
years, Synergy has experienced explosive growth with landmark
acquisitions and Omni-channel revenue growth. 


Leadership Team






Jack Ross
Chairman & CEO
More +



Mr. Ross is a serial entrepreneur, investor and Director with over 25 years of experience in senior level roles at multiple consumer product goods companies. Over his tenure, Mr. Ross has developed a broad and diverse network of retail contacts at senior management levels across North America. He brings with him a wealth of knowledge from leading Start-ups to public companies and adds corporate governance experience from both Public and Private sectors.








Jaime Fickett
SVP - Finance & Operations
More +



Ms. Fickett oversees all aspects of Synergy’s Finance and Operations.  An accountant with over 17 years experience and a strong background in auditing, she handles all the financial reporting and logistics.  She has been with the FOCUSfactor brand for over ten years.  Ms. Fickett received her bachelor’s degree in Accounting from The University of Maine and is currently enrolled in a Masters of Science in Accounting program.








Al Baumeler
EVP - Sales & Marketing Retail
More +



Mr Baumeler served as the Senior Vice President of Marketing for HNS Global before joining Synergy CHC in 2015. He was Chief Marketing Officer at Natrol where he oversaw Marketing, Sales, and New Product Development in a portfolio that included vitamin supplements and sports nutrition brands. Prior to HNS, he was Vice President of Marketing at Rexall. Prior to Rexall, he held various leadership positions in Marketing with Novartis, Wyeth and Reckitt Benckiser. Mr. Baumeler received his bachelor’s degree in Engineering from Rutgers University and an MBA from Columbia Business School.








Greg Hollohan
VP - Sales & Marketing Canada
More +



Mr. Hollohan brings 30 years of global consumer products industry experience to Synergy. He has achieved success working for some of the world’s best branded organizations; Kraft Foods, Gillette/Procter & Gamble, Moosehead Breweries, Nike and SunOpta. He has led teams for both branded, private label, and large contract manufacturing partners. In his most recent role as Vice President of Sales & Marketing for Life Science Nutritionals, Mr. Hollohan helped grow the businesses of branded and contract business by 22% prior to the parent being sold in 2015. Mr. Hollohan brings a brand focused, customer-centric, and collaborative approach to both business and strategic customer leadership. Mr. Hollohan is a graduate of the University of New Brunswick.






The Synergy Effect Team






Andy Davies
Chief Operations Officer
More +



Mr Davies is the COO at The Synergy Effect, and is responsible for executing the Company’s online strategy. Key areas that he specializes in include e-commerce, business development, digital strategy and revenue growth. Prior to this Mr Davies was a co-founder of NomadChoice Pty Ltd (Flat Tummy Tea), where he was Head of Influencer Marketing and contributed heavily to growing revenue by a multiple of 20 in just 18 months. He has held positions in Consumer Product Sales, Property Investment and Accounting at various companies prior to that. Mr Davies graduated with a Bachelor of Business from the University of Tasmania, where he majored in Accounting and Management.








Johannes Weirather
Chief Digital Officer
More +



Mr Weirather is the CDO at The Synergy Effect, and his primary areas of expertise are in digital strategy and growth, project management, customer journey management and team building. Mr Weirather formerly held the position of General Manager at NomadChoice Pty Ltd (Flat Tummy Tea) and has extensive experience in Project Management, Social Media Management and International Market Development. He holds a Masters Degree of Marketing, Strategic Management and International Business from the University of Innsbruck.








Valentina Barron
Head of Social Media Marketing
More +



Ms Barron is the Head of Social Media Marketing at The Synergy Effect. She is responsible for creating and executing exceptional content across social media, contributing to brand innovation and running larger campaigns across our various owned media platforms. Ms Barron was formerly the Head of Social Media Marketing at NomadChoice Pty Ltd (Flat Tummy Tea) and was a key player in growing and optimizing key social and email assets. She graduated from the University of Western Australia with a double degree in Science and Commerce, majoring in Psychology, Marketing and Employment Relations.








Ben Little
Chief Innovation Officer - Influencer Marketing
More +



Mr Little is the CIO at The Synergy Effect, with focus on influencer marketing. His areas of specialization include high-level influencer marketing strategy, social media innovation, budgeting and ROI analysis. Mr Little formerly held the role of Influencer Marketer at NomadChoice Pty Ltd (Flat Tummy Tea) where he set new records and was consistently the top performer. Prior to that, Mr Little worked in Property Investment, Banking and Taxation. He studied a Bachelor of Business at the University of Tasmania, majoring in Accounting and Entrepreneurship.








Danielle Grandy
Head of Customer Experience
More +



Mrs Grandy is the Head of Customer Experience at The Synergy Effect, and is responsible for optimizing customer experience, implementing innovation, and capitalizing on customer lifetime value, as well as managing a global customer experience team. She formerly worked in Customer Experience Management, and also held the position of PR & Communications Coordinator at Nova Scotia Nature Trust. In addition, she holds a double degree in Arts and Public Relations from Mount Saint Vincent University.








Kyle Ross
Head of Influencer Marketing
More +



Mr K.Ross is the Head of Influencer Marketing at The Synergy Effect. He’s a major growth driver and his areas of specialization include media buying and conversion optimization, as well as the building and overseeing of a highly-trained team. Mr K.Ross holds a Bachelor of Science from Plymouth State University.






Board of Directors






Jack Ross
Chairman & CEO
More +



Mr. Ross is a serial entrepreneur, investor and Director with over 25 years of experience in senior level roles at multiple consumer product goods companies. Over his tenure, Mr. Ross has developed a broad and diverse network of retail contacts at senior management levels across North America. He brings with him a wealth of knowledge from leading Start-ups to public companies and adds corporate governance experience from both Public and Private sectors.








Paul Sorelle
Director
More +



Mr. Paul SoRelle, age 58, is a member of the Company’s Board of Directors to hold such position until the Company’s next annual meeting of its’ stockholders or until his successor(s) are duly elected and qualified. Since November 1999, Mr. SoRelle has been the CEO and Managing Partner of Pioneer Press of Greeley, Inc., a commercial offset printing company. Prior to joining Pioneer Press, Mr. SoRelle worked in the gaming business as well as the retail gasoline and convenience store business.








Stephen Fryer
Director
More +



Mr. Stephen Fryer, age 76, as a member of the Company’s Board of Directors, to hold such position until the Company’s next annual meeting of its’ stockholders or until his successor(s) are duly elected and qualified. Since April 2003, Mr. Fryer has been the CEO and Managing Partner of SC Capital Partners, Inc., a private micro-market investment banking and private equity intermediary. Prior to joining SC Capital Partners, Inc., Mr. Fryer was a consulting investment banker with Grant Bettingen, Inc., a broker-dealer based in California, from January 2001 to March 2003. From May 1989 to August 1997, Mr. Fryer was the Principal and Managing Director of Ventana International, Ltd., a venture capital and private investment banking firm with operations and investors in the United States, Latin America, Europe and Asia. Mr. Fryer earned a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering, with a minor in Economics, from the University of Southern California.






Advisory Board






Jeffrey Kadanoff

More +



Previously the principal with Bain & Company where he served as a strategy consultant for 14 years, Mr. Kadanoff has worked as CFO, a consulting engineer at Hatch and VP strategic planning and development. He holds a B. Eng. with Distinction in Chemical Engineering and a Minor in Management from McGill University and an M.B.A. with Distinction from INSEAD. Additionally, Mr. Kadanoff is a licenced member of Professional Engineers Ontario.








Tim Polmear

More +



Tim is an entrepreneur, investor and corporate advisor with a particular focus on identifying opportunities to create scalable brands for the digital age through social media and strategic branding. In 2013, Tim co-founded highly successful ecommerce company, Flat Tummy Tea (acquired by Synergy CHC 2015) and has since developed new ecommerce brand, Sneaky Vaunt.








Bec Polmear

More +



Co-founder of globally renowned ecommerce company Flat Tummy Tea. Specialist in creative brand application, copywriting, social media marketing and brand strategy. Bec co-creates new and innovative ecommerce brands, ready to launch and scale. Recent projects include ecommerce company Sneaky Vaunt, acquired by Synergy CHC.










